##  Dynamic Groups & Rule Syntax

### Example Rules
```txt
user.jobTitle - startsWith "xyz"
user.department - eq "Developer"
user.companyName - ne "companyname"
Operators
Operator	Meaning
startsWith	Starts with
eq	Equals
ne	Not equals


Connectors
AND → All rules must be true

OR → At least one rule must be true

 Group Ownership & Nesting Behavior
The owner of a group can only manage users within that specific group.
They do not automatically gain admin rights outside that group.

Members of assigned groups can be manually added or removed.

Dynamic groups cannot have manual members.

Dynamic groups can be nested under other groups,
but no group can be nested under a dynamic group.

Code
Security Group
   ↓
[Dynamic] SG2   ✖ SG3 (cannot nest under dynamic)
 Role Assignments & Group Nesting
Assigned groups with role assignments do not allow nesting inside them.

Example:

SG2 has a User Administrator role assignment

Anyone added to SG2 automatically becomes a User Administrator

Code
Assigned SG1 ← Role Assignment → Assigned SG2 ← Assigned SG3
Dynamic groups can be nested under assigned groups,
but cannot have groups nested under themselves.

 Microsoft Entra ID Registered Devices (BYOD)
Microsoft Entra ID supports Bring Your Own Device (BYOD).

Users connect to the company’s Entra tenant using MDM tools like Intune.

Users can access company resources while keeping personal files/apps private.

Supported OS: Windows 10/11, iOS, Android, macOS

 Microsoft Entra Hybrid Joined Devices
Policies can be pushed using MEMMS and Conditional Access.

Supported OS: Windows 10 & 11  
(Home editions not supported)

Hybrid Join Diagram
Code
