 Custom Security Attributes (CSA)
Overview
Feature available under P1/P2 licenses.

Global Administrator must assign themselves one of the following roles:

Attribute Assignment Administrator

Attribute Definition Administrator

Attribute Assignment Reader

Lab Example
Created attribute set: CC (Security Clearance Level)

Description: Access control for HR team

Values:

Level 1 - Low

Level 2 - Medium

Level 3 - High

 Custom Security Attributes - Key Concepts
Custom attributes are key-value pairs assigned to:

Users

Enterprise Applications / Service Principals

They enable:
Fine-grained access control

Object categorization

Secure storage of sensitive profile data

Use Cases
Advanced Access Control  
Tag apps/service principals for Conditional Access filtering.

HR Data Integration  
Store employee data (clearance level, project team, employee type).

Data Privacy  
Restrict visibility to authorized administrators only.

 Exam Notes (Critical)
Global Administrator cannot read, define, or assign custom security attributes.

CSAs can only be assigned to users and enterprise apps/service principals.

Scope delegation must be attribute-set specific, not tenant-wide.

CSAs and attribute sets cannot be deleted (deactivate only).

CSAs and attribute sets cannot be renamed (only descriptions can change).

CSAs cannot be used in dynamic group rules.

CSAs can be used in Conditional Access (ABAC).

 Conditional Access Example (ABAC)
Block access to any enterprise app where:
CustomSecurityAttribute.Sensitivity = High  
AND the user is outside the corporate network.
